The new issue of the IIS Yearbook is compiled of articles integrated by a broad theme designated in its title as “Actual Problems of Modern World Politics”, and is divided into five sections.
The first section includes papers devoted to economy and policy of the countries of the Caucasus. It also contains the report on results of situation analysis of the state of affairs in the region.
Another contribution to the section suggests justification and a general outline of the research
project aimed at elaboration of the Index of the Caucasus database. The second section includes
comprisess papers whose authors address the analysis of ceaselessly disturbing situation in the
Middle East. The third section is devoted to European policy – including the EU course towards
the Caucasian countries. In the fourth section their vision of world politics is proposed by the
authors that have, besides extensive scholarly knowledge, also the invaluable experience of practical diplomatic work which allows them to amalgamate academic knowledge with diplomatic
experience in their analysis of the modern world. In the fifth section those aspects of international
relations are considered which are born by scientific and technical development, as well as trends
in the development of sociopolitical knowledge and their influence on world politics. These are
problems of militarization of space, informatization and the threats associated with them, and
also various facets of the “soft power”, in understanding of which the authors of the Yearbook
show a wide variety of approaches.
