Summary
The article analyzes the inner political situation in the Republic of South Ossetia in early 2014, on
the eve of the forthcoming parliamentary elections. Two years after the last presidential elections in the
Republic, South Ossetia has not managed to overcome a social-economic and political crises. It failed
not only to reorganize its economy on the lines of sustainable development, but start modernization
and reforms at all. A plan for economic revival of the Republic does not exist. There is no national
program of state establishment either. For the local political elite there is still an open question –
whether the Republic of South Ossetia heads to the reunification with the North Ossetia, towards
integration into Russia, or towards creation of a full-fledged national state. At the present moment
neither the situation in the Republic has been stabilized, nor the South Ossetian society has been
consolidated. At the helm there is a rather ill-matched and hardly capable of functioning coalition
government. Political forces are mainly engaged in getting ready for the parliamentary elections,
and not in developing alternative and realistic programs for the Republic’s way forward. Today a lot
depends on the role of Moscow that has all the opportunities to influence the ongoing processes in the
Republic. At the same time a lot still depends on the South Ossetian society itself.
Key Words: The Republic of South Ossetia, National program of state establishment, Parliamentary
elections.
