Summary
The article presents the MGIMO database of quantitative and qualitative political information
on the South Caucasus (“Caucasus Index”). The database is designed as an analytical tool for
researchers who study the international situation and politics in the region. The database includes
information about the events taking place in the South Caucasus. A special matrix of event description
is designed that allows to analyze mass media messages and data from other sources in a systematic
way. So the qualitative data extracted from media is encoded in formally structured event descriptions.
In the future it is expected for the database to include quantitative data (economics, demographics,
etc.). Besides, a systematic model to describe the complex political events, systems and institutions
(elections, party systems, individual parties, etc.) is planned to be added. A library of analytical
materials about the South Caucasus is also supposed to be developed as a part of the project.
Key Words: Database, event, event analysis, South Caucasus, Caucasus, Azerbaijan, Armenia,
Georgia, Abkhazia, South Ossetia, index, politics, economics, international relations.
