Summary
The paper touches upon the issue of Iranian influence on the internal political conflict in Syria.
An analysis of the strategic partnership between Iran and Syria and the behavior of Iranin the
Syrian conflict is suggested. The main emphasis is put on the geopolitical issues of Syrian-Iranian
partnership.
A special attention is paid to external causes of Syrian revolt including projects of the gas pipeline
building through the Syrian territory. The author considers the Iranian aid to the government of
Bashar al-Assad during the civil war in Syria.
The article deals also with the consequences of the Syrian conflict for the geopolitical situation of
the Middle East and Iran.
Key Words: Iran, Syria, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, internal conflict, civil war, geopolitical situation,
geopolitical rivalry, Sunni-Shia contradictions, gas pipeline.
