of Economic and Monetary Union Functioning
after Adoption of the EURO
Irina Pashkovskaya, Doct. of Political Sciences, Ph.D. in Law,
Leading Research Fellow, Center for Euro-Atlantic Security,
Institute for International Studies, MGIMO-University
119454, 76 Vernadsky Ave, Moscow, Russia.
Summary
The EU experience of further providing the Economic and Monetary Union with actual political
and legal framework after the introduction of the single currency euro is of extreme importance
because of the fact that this activity defines future European Union parameters in the long perspective.
This political and legislative process does not only regulate economic and monetary integration of the
EU Member States, but also significantly affects development of the EU relations with the Russian
Federation. The results of economic and monetary integration of the EU Member States vividly
demonstrate that only mutually and together states are capable of withstanding global challenges of
our time and lead their peoples to prosperity.
Key Words: European Union, Economic and Monetary Union, euro, European Central Bank,
Stability and Growth Pact.
