Summary
The article deals with the causes and possible consequences of the announced reform of the
National Security Agency (NSA) by U.S. President Barack Obama on January 17, 2014. The main
reason for this induced political step were revelations by former NSA employee Edward J. Snowden
of total espionage system, created the United States and the ensuing international response to these
revelations.
Key Words: U.S. foreign policy, the NSA, the CIA, cyber security, President Barack Obama,
E. Snowden, XKeyscore program, Prism program, Review Group on Intelligence and Communications.
